on.com/Cool-Cities-Sovereignty-Global-Warming/dp/0300224206/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*The Death and Life of Great American Cities*","blurb":"Widely considered the most influential urbanist of the twentieth century, Jane Jacobs argued forcefully for a rethinking of city renewal. She understood the critical role of social capital in shaping urban resilience. While lacking a university degree, she was a first-rate intellectual and a grassroots leader –a rare woman in a male-dominated field of urban planning.","note":"Jane Jacobs\r\nVintage, 1992","link_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Death-Life-Great-American-Cities/dp/067974195X/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"EXPLORE","headline":"Fragile Cities Visualization","blurb":"Working with the United Nations and other partners like xSeer, the Igarapé Institute developed an interactive data visualization to track risks in more than 2,100 cities around the world. The platform features eleven risks that shape fragility in cities, allowing users to track changes between 2000-2015 and predict future trends until 2030.","note":" Igarapé Institute","link_url":"https://igarape.org.br/en/apps/fragile-cities-data-visualization/","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":""},{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*The New Urban Crisis*","blurb":"Described as the [rockstar of (urban) regeneration](https://www.theguardian.com/cities/2017/oct/26/gentrification-richard-florida-interview-creative-class-new-urban-crisis), Richard Florida shot to fame in the early 2000s arguing about the importance of fostering “creative classes” in cities. In his latest book, Florida revisits his earlier assumptions, warning of the ways growing inequality and exclusion are expanding in some of the 